{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-a1ad32e6c7ccd763", "type": "tool_result", "content": "Paper 2607.14749 not found\n===\n# UniMoE-Audio: Unified Speech and Music Generation with Dynamic-Capacity MoE\narXiv: 2510.13344\nAuthors: Zhenyu Liu, Yunxin Li, Xuanyu Zhang, Qixun Teng, Shenyuan Jiang, Xinyu Chen, Haoyuan Shi, Jinchao Li, Qi Wang, Haolan Chen, Fanbo Meng, Mingjun Zhao, Yu Xu, Yancheng He, Baotian Hu, Min Zhang\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We propose UniMoE-Audio, a unified speech and music generation model based on a novel Dynamic-Capacity MoE framework that integrates a Top-P routing strategy and a hybrid expert design to mitigate inherent task conflict.\n  2. We introduce a data-aware, three-stage training curriculum that systematically overcomes data imbalance through independent specialist training, router warmup, and synergistic joint training.\n  3. We provide extensive experiments demonstrating that UniMoE-Audio achieves state-of-the-art or competitive performance on major speech and music generation benchmarks while revealing valuable insights into the dynamic activation patterns of the unified MoE model.\n\nTags: TTS\n===\n# InstructAudio: Unified speech and music generation with natural language instruction\narXiv: 2511.18487\nAuthors: Chunyu Qiang, Kang Yin, Xiaopeng Wang, Yuzhe Liang, Jiahui Zhao, Ruibo Fu, Tianrui Wang, Cheng Gong, Chen Zhang, Longbiao Wang, Jianwu Dang\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We introduce a joint modeling framework for speech and music generation based on a multimodal diffusion transformer architecture.\n  2. We achieve unified text-based control over speech and music generation through a standardized instruction-phoneme input format encompassing timbre, paralinguistic, and musical attributes while supporting dialogue generation.\n  3. Experimental results demonstrate state-of-the-art performance in instruction-based text-to-speech while maintaining competitive text-to-music capabilities.\n\nTags: TTS, TTS/架构-NAR-Flow, TTS/控制-NL描述, TTS/控制-指令合成, 压缩, 压缩/量化-VAE", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "c4a8a567-174d-4233-ad1b-5d3d54c2f6f0", "uuid": "48b9cd77-c9b7-46a9-8f7a-01938daba837", "timestamp": "2026-07-17T07:00:07.638Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "Paper 2607.14749 not found\n===\n# UniMoE-Audio: Unified Speech and Music Generation with Dynamic-Capacity MoE\narXiv: 2510.13344\nAuthors: Zhenyu Liu, Yunxin Li, Xuanyu Zhang, Qixun Teng, Shenyuan Jiang, Xinyu Chen, Haoyuan Shi, Jinchao Li, Qi Wang, Haolan Chen, Fanbo Meng, Mingjun Zhao, Yu Xu, Yancheng He, Baotian Hu, Min Zhang\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We propose UniMoE-Audio, a unified speech and music generation model based on a novel Dynamic-Capacity MoE framework that integrates a Top-P routing strategy and a hybrid expert design to mitigate inherent task conflict.\n  2. We introduce a data-aware, three-stage training curriculum that systematically overcomes data imbalance through independent specialist training, router warmup, and synergistic joint training.\n  3. We provide extensive experiments demonstrating that UniMoE-Audio achieves state-of-the-art or competitive performance on major speech and music generation benchmarks while revealing valuable insights into the dynamic activation patterns of the unified MoE model.\n\nTags: TTS\n===\n# InstructAudio: Unified speech and music generation with natural language instruction\narXiv: 2511.18487\nAuthors: Chunyu Qiang, Kang Yin, Xiaopeng Wang, Yuzhe Liang, Jiahui Zhao, Ruibo Fu, Tianrui Wang, Cheng Gong, Chen Zhang, Longbiao Wang, Jianwu Dang\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We introduce a joint modeling framework for speech and music generation based on a multimodal diffusion transformer architecture.\n  2. We achieve unified text-based control over speech and music generation through a standardized instruction-phoneme input format encompassing timbre, paralinguistic, and musical attributes while supporting dialogue generation.\n  3. Experimental results demonstrate state-of-the-art performance in instruction-based text-to-speech while maintaining competitive text-to-music capabilities.\n\nTags: TTS, TTS/架构-NAR-Flow, TTS/控制-NL描述, TTS/控制-指令合成, 压缩, 压缩/量化-VAE", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
